article.headline: East Tennessee State 75, Lipscomb 72
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Reserve Dequan Twilley hit a 3-pointer with two seconds left in overtime to lead East Tennessee State to a 75-72 victory Thursday night over Lipscomb. Twilley had missed a jumper at the buzzer of regulation that would have won it for East Tennessee (9-7, 3-1 Atlantic Sun Conference). The winning basket was his only score from the field all night as he finished with 7 points. Eddie Ard scored 24 points for Lipscomb (8-7, 2-2) including a 3-pointer with 1:14 left in overtime that tied it 72-72. Mike Smith led East Tennessee with 17 points and eight rebounds, including two free throws with 1:30 left that pushed the Bucs ahead 70-68. Courtney Pigram added 15 points for the Bucs and Andrew Reed scored 13 and had eight rebounds. Brian Fisk added 18 points for Lipscomb, making 6-of-9 from the floor and all 3 3-pointers. Lipscomb led 32-31 at halftime.
